{
  "bookId": "laozi-wangbi-wiki",
  "num": 64,
  "title": "第六十四章",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "其安易持，其未兆易謀。"
    },
    {
      "text": "其脆易泮，其微易散。"
    },
    {
      "text": "為之於未有，"
    },
    {
      "text": "治之於未亂。"
    },
    {
      "text": "合抱之木，生於毫末；九層之臺，起於累土；千里之行，始於足下。為者敗之，執者失之。"
    },
    {
      "text": "是以聖人無為故無敗，無執故無失。民之從事，常於幾成而敗之。"
    },
    {
      "text": "慎終如始，則無敗事。是以聖人欲不欲，不貴難得之貨；"
    },
    {
      "text": "學不學，復眾人之所過。"
    },
    {
      "text": "以輔萬物之自然，而不敢為。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "wangbi": [
      {
        "id": "wangbi-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 11
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "以其安不忘危，持之不忘亡，謀之無功之勢，故曰易也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 10
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "雖失無入有，以其微脆之故，未足以興大功，故易也。此四者，皆說慎終也。不可以無之故而不持，不可以微之故而弗散也。無而弗持則生有焉，微而不散則生大焉。故慮終之患，如始之禍，則無敗事。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "謂其安未兆也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "謂微脆也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 40
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "當以慎終除微，慎微除亂，而以施為治之，形名執之，反生事原，巧辟滋作，故敗失也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 29
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "不慎終也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 6,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 25
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "好欲雖微，爭尚為之，興難得之貨雖細，貪盜為之起也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "wangbi-8",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 7,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 11
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "不學而能者，自然也，喻於不學者，過也。故學不學，以復眾人之過。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
